2825:middlewares/freertos/source/queue.c ****         /* Only do anything if there are no messages in the queue.  This function
2826:middlewares/freertos/source/queue.c ****          *  will not actually cause the task to block, just place it on a blocked
2827:middlewares/freertos/source/queue.c ****          *  list.  It will not block until the scheduler is unlocked - at which
2828:middlewares/freertos/source/queue.c ****          *  time a yield will be performed.  If an item is added to the queue while
2829:middlewares/freertos/source/queue.c ****          *  the queue is locked, and the calling task blocks on the queue, then the
2830:middlewares/freertos/source/queue.c ****          *  calling task will be immediately unblocked when the queue is unlocked. */
